      },
      "date": "2014-12-21 03:40:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs this valid for multi-hop configurations?\n\nSay you have a client on gni0, a router with gni0 and o2ib0, a router with o2ib0 and tcp0, and a server with tcp0.  Since the client's first router doesn't have a tcp0 interface, will this mark the route unusable?\n\nAdmittedly, I think multi-hop configs are rare.  I'm not aware of us using it at ORNL. Maybe it make sense to have a config for this (multi-hop off by default, turning it on disables this check).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
