        "subject": "LU-6060 lnet: set downis to 1 if there's no NI for remote net",
        "message": "LU-6060 lnet: set downis to 1 if there's no NI for remote net\n\nlnet_route_t::lr_downis is marked as zero even if there is no NI to\ntarget network, this is wrong and breaks logic of ARF.\nThis patch fixes this problem, and also removes obsolete code for\nptllnd.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I9aab63110d7526ab30a98421e663cf66b7ee8cf2\n"
